KoreanFlashCardApp Implementation Checklist

1. Fix the app foundation
- Make `App` resolve and return the DI-created `AppShell` instead of creating a new unmanaged instance.
- Verify `WordProvider.LoadData()` runs once at startup and does not duplicate words on repeated app launches.
- Un-comment or replace the `BasePage` template only if it is still needed; otherwise remove dead scaffolding.

2. Finish the data and service layer
- Complete `FlashCardProvider` so it can build quiz sessions from the loaded word list.
- Fix `ProgressProvider.LoadProgressAsync()` so it does not overwrite loaded progress with an empty list.
- Make `SaveProgressAsync()` persist changes after updating progress.
- Register any missing providers in dependency injection.

3. Define the MVP screen flow
- Decide the minimum page flow: module selection -> flashcard session -> answer result -> next card.
- Keep the first release to one learning module for TOPIK vocabulary instead of designing for every future mode.
- Add routing for each page in `AppShell`.

4. Build the WordDefinition Header
- Create a reusable header component or content view for the active word.
- Show the Korean term, word type, and supporting definition text.
- Make this the visual anchor for study and review pages.

5. Build the module page
- Create the module page listed in `ThingsToDo.odt`.
- Show available study modules, word counts, and progress status.
- Make this the first meaningful screen instead of the current placeholder main page.
- Each should be split off into 15 words.

6. Build the flashcard session page
- Show one target word at a time.
- Generate answer choices from words with the same `Word_Type_ID`.
- Add submit, reveal answer, next card, and session completion states.

7. Implement pacing and review logic
- Keep the current 1, 2, 4 day pattern as the initial spacing rule.
- Filter sessions so due words appear before new words.
- Record correct and incorrect outcomes separately if you want pacing to improve later.

8. Replace placeholder UI
- Remove the .NET bot image, test title, and sample welcome copy from `MainPage`.
- Replace placeholder shell title labels with real app navigation and screen titles.
- Apply the existing resource dictionaries consistently across the new screens.

9. Validate the model against the original design notes
- Confirm `Word`, `Translation`, and `Definition` still match the intent in `KoreanFlashCardApp.odt`.
- Decide whether `Translation.Translation_Word` should point to `Word` instead of `Translation`.
- Review naming consistency for `Word_Name`, `Definition_Description`, and enum-backed IDs.

10. Prepare for sync later without blocking MVP
- Keep local JSON progress storage for the first working release.
- Define a future sync contract for user progress, devices, and conflict handling.
- Do not add backend complexity until the single-device learning flow works end to end.

11. Add verification
- Build the solution after each major milestone.
- Add a small testable surface for option generation and progress date calculation.
- Run at least one manual session on device or Windows target to verify navigation and persistence.

Suggested execution order
- First: steps 1, 2, and 8
- Next: steps 3, 4, 5, and 6
- Then: steps 7 and 11
- Later: steps 9 and 10
